```julia
function clean_column(col::String)
    return lowercase(strip(col)) |> replace('-', '_') |> replace(r"\s+", "_")
end
```

This function first lowercases and strips leading and trailing whitespaces from the column name. Then it replaces hyphens with underscores. Finally, it replaces all sequences of one or more whitespace characters with a single underscore. This ensures that the column name is converted to a standardized format with only lowercase letters and underscores.
